WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.169
Today we will learn about bud grafting. Bud grafting is when we

2
00:00:04.169 --> 00:00:08.339
take a single bud from one plant and attach it to another plant.

3
00:00:08.339 --> 00:00:12.345
Why do we bud graft? It uses only one bud instead of

4
00:00:12.345 --> 00:00:16.352
a whole branch. This saves plant material and has a high success rate.

5
00:00:16.352 --> 00:00:21.140
Step one. Choose a healthy bud from the parent plant. Use a sharp knife

6
00:00:21.140 --> 00:00:25.928
to cut a small shield shape around the bud, including a thin layer of wood.

7
00:00:25.928 --> 00:00:29.837
Step two. On the rootstock, make a T-shaped cut in the bark.

8
00:00:29.837 --> 00:00:33.746
This is called a T-cut. Gently lift the flaps of bark open.

9
00:00:33.746 --> 00:00:37.915
Step three. Slide the bud shield into the T-cut on the rootstock.

10
00:00:37.915 --> 00:00:42.085
Push it down gently until it fits snugly under the bark flaps.

11
00:00:42.085 --> 00:00:46.450
Step four. Wrap the graft tightly with budding tape. Leave the bud

12
00:00:46.450 --> 00:00:50.814
exposed so it can grow. The tape keeps everything moist and secure.

13
00:00:50.814 --> 00:00:55.407
After a few weeks, the bud starts to grow into a new shoot. The bud

14
00:00:55.407 --> 00:01:00.000
graft is a success! Well done Caleb, now you know how to do bud grafting.


